Enjoy the marina views out of your primary bedroom. Exclusive amenities include tennis courts, pickleball courts, waterfront parks, and a clubhouse. Washington Park is within walking distance, offering 220 acres of trails, camping, and a boat ramp. This condo is a perfect blend of convenience and coastal charm. Sold as-is.

Brand new affordable manufactured home on 1.9 acres close to the Skagit River, Sauk Mountain, and hiking trails (Rockport State Park, Sauk Mountain, and Howard Miller Park). Across the road, you can launch your boat at Howard Miller Park. Full RV parking and full RV hookups plus room to build a garage/shop, shed, or carport. The seller has applied for a building permit so a 24' x 36' Shop with 864 sq. ft. and Two 10' x 10' doors can be built. The permit is pending approval with Skagit County. The buyer can build the shop as soon as the permit is approved. Nice setting with woods surrounding you. Only 35 minutes to Sedro Woolley.

Location! Location! Location! 4 bedrooms, 2 bath, rambler home recently updated, kitchen, double pane windows, laminate flooring, not carpet, updated showers. Potential for duplex/office/daycare, many possibilities. Property with good advertising exposure to high traffic on Burlington Blvd. Large lot of approx 8040 sq/ft with alley access and newly built duplexes directly behind. Large 2 car garage w/ loads of storage, shop space and a fenced backyard. Buyer to contact the city of Burlington and/or website for specific and permitted uses. Access to the back alley for convenient RV parking. No HOA. Located out of the flood zone. This is a must see!!

Don't miss out on this exceptional opportunity to own a piece of the highly sought-after Blanchard Knob Community. This parcel offers breathtaking panoramic views of the Skagit flats, Samish Bay, protected farmlands, the charming town of Edison, the Salish Sea, and the San Juan Islands. The community provides its own water system, fiber optic cabling, and is bordered by State-owned forest land, ensuring both privacy and access to recreational activities. Additionally, the lot is fully serviced with power and water, and comes with an approved 3-bedroom septic system design. Experience a world-class community, stunning views, and an outstanding property all in one place.

Bring your plans to build in La Conner's desirable Shelter Bay Community. Great location on a quiet street and near all community amenities including boat launch, tennis & pickleball courts, golf course, parks, community beach and more. All utilities available in street for an easy build. Marina with preferred moorage rates for Shelter Bay owners. On leased land.

Huge views from this perfect cottage on the hill. There is so much packed into this property! Start with the brand new deck and charming entrance...this welcoming home features a huge fireplace, dining room, nice sized kitchen with a walk-in pantry. Wait, the carport has a patio sitting area and...wait for it, a shop in the back...and did I mention the gardens...flowers everywhere!!! There is no detail missed. New roof in 2020.

Bring your plans and build! This breathtaking 4.6 acre property nestled in the mountains is ready to bring your vision to life. This level, cleared lot offers you the tranquility of living among the wildlife. Close to Marblemounts rural amenities and all the outdoor activities the Cascades and Skagit River can offer. Power in the street. Welcome to your nature getaway!

Beautiful 2448 SQFT spacious home with 4 bedrooms and 3 full bathrooms in a quiet sought after neighborhood of Forest Hills. This home is only a minutes drive to downtown Anacortes. Close proximity to popular Anacortes Community Forest Land trails. This is a must see home and an amazing opportunity to not miss out on!

Two rare Burlington short plated lots for sale! (P62510 next door also available, listing #221758.) .48 acre each, water and power on Gardner. These are considered county lots - city lots are across the street. Zoned Urban Reserve Residential (URR) which allows for a single-family dwelling and ADU, manufactured homes OK as well. (Buyer to verify.) Owners have critical area review approval letter. Lot certification complete with recording documents submitted to county. Perc test complete, onsite sewage permit approved as well. Lots are cleared, flat and ready for your new home build. Purchase one, purchase both!

Nearly 4 acres of pristine, deed land in La Conner awaits you. Step into your private oasis enveloped by majestic trees. This 3-bed, 1-bath home is tucked away on a tranquil private road. Enjoy a spacious porch and a generous yard perfect for chickens, gardening, or hosting gatherings. On the front half of the property, discover an old cabin, RV hookups (w/ power and water), a garage, and several additional outbuildings scattered throughout. Just a short drive from the water and only 2.5 miles from downtown La Conner, known for its vibrant art scene, cute boutique shops, farm-to-table dining, and acclaimed marinaa gateway to the San Juan Islands. Convenient access to I-5 makes commuting to Seattle, Vancouver, or BC a breeze.

Lake View! This approx 1.15 acre lot has a view of the lake through the trees and a 24' x 32' shop on it. Water, electricity, sewer and natural gas are in the street. Buyer to verify utilities and connection fees, etc. This is close to the Big Lake public boat launch for lake access.

Experience luxury living w/protected views of Burrows Bay, Islands & Skyline Marina! This stunning home features vaulted ceilings, exposed beams & HW floors.The main level's beautifully updated kitchen is perfect for entertaining. Sliding French doors lead to an expansive deck, seamlessly blending the kitchen, living & dining spaces w/breathtaking views as your focal point. The main level includes 2 bdrms joined by a Jack-n-Jill bath & primary suite w/water views. 2nd living area, bdrm & bath on lower level. Enjoy the privacy of Cypress trees, a grassy area for play, new retaining wall, fully fenced & landscaped. 2-car garage & upper parking spaces. Skyline's amenities; private beach, park, tennis & pickleball courts, cabanas & boat moorage!

Welcome to Brickyard Park a 55+ Community in Sedro Woolley! This is a 2 bed + den/1.75 ba new home. Enter the home with a no step entry. The home has 36 wide doorways. There are over $22, 000 in upgrades in this home. This home has a great room w/gas fireplace. The kitchen has select cabinets, quartz counters, a gas range, & SS appliances. Other upgrades in this home are the lights, plumbing fixtures & carpet. Primary ensuite has wic, a tile shower in bath w/tile floors, & quartz counters. ADA toilets in both bathrooms. Mini splits for heat/cool. There is a 2 car garage. Covered rear patio. Clubhouse with an almost 1 acre park w/walking trail around it, pickleball, bocce ball, horseshoes & an area for lawn games.

Discover a breathtaking retreat nestled on just over 1.6 acres, boasting panoramic territorial & water vistas. Step inside to be greeted by the allure of bamboo flooring, accentuated by the warmth of wood columns and beams. Cozy up beside by the wood-burning fireplace, ensuring warmth & comfort. The gourmet kitchen, an epicurean's delight, commands attention with its seamless flow into the inviting living room. Outside, an expansive deck beckons, complete with an outdoor fireplace, inviting hot tub, & ample seating, offering a serene oasis for relaxation & enjoyment. RV or boat parking on the side of the garage caters to your adventurous spirit. Welcome to your own slice of paradise, where luxury and tranquility converge in perfect harmony.

Opportunity awaits with this 4.3 acre property conveniently located right off of Highway 9. A blank slate to bring your vision to life, this wooded property is ready for your plans. Create your PNW Oasis in the heart of the peaceful Prairie community, still with close access to Sedro Woolleys historic downtown with shops, restaurants and more! Access easement available. Well is allowed. Buyer will need to investigate utility availability.

Embrace the opportunity to restore this unique custom tri-level home in Shelter Bay, La Conner! Featuring a distinctive design with an abundance of wood elements, this fixer-upper offers endless potential. Situated on a spacious lot bordered by greenbelt on two sides and just two blocks from the community beach, the location is ideal for coastal living. Inside, vaulted ceilings and skylights create a bright and airy atmosphere. The home includes four bedrooms and a beautiful bonus space on the top level. Unlock the possibilities of this special property and envision the transformation into your dream coastal retreat. Don't miss outschedule a showing today to explore the potential of this Shelter Bay gem!

Discover perfection in this pristine home. Every inch reflects the utmost care & quality. Enjoy a gourmet kitchen with dual pantries open to the living room. Also featuring a family room, & grand primary suite with private, retreat space & oversized bathroom with huge garden tub. Perfect separation of spaces. Meticulously maintained inside & out. Endless potential with the 5-bay shop with; power, water, septic, craft room & a den/office for all your hobbies & needs. Surrounded by serene woods, meadows, & trails, the estate offers lush gardens, a fire pit area, & a charming garden shed/playhouseall in complete privacy, away from neighboring eyes. A haven of peace awaits you here. New roof & well pump with abundant, amazing-tasting water.

Truly one of a kind! Extraordinary waterfront building site with almost 17 acres, and nearly 3000+/- feet of waterfront. The property features spectacular westerly views of the Puget Sound, and San Juan islands and offers the ultimate estate setting to build your dream home. A water catchment system will most likely be needed as well as an advanced septic system. Extensive buyer due diligence will be required. This is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to own a substantial waterfront property with obstructed marine and island views in the beautiful Pacific Northwest.

Come build your dream home on a cul-de-sac on beautiful Burlington Hill! Located in a gorgeous neighborhood of custom homes with easy access to Burlington, Mount Vernon and I-5. Panoramic views of Skagit Valley and the Cascade Mountain Range!

Two rare Burlington short plated lots for sale! (P62516 next door also available, listing #2214759.) .48 acre each, water and power on Gardner Rd. These are considered county lots - city lots are across the street. Zoned Urban Reserve Residential (URR) which allows for a single-family dwelling and ADU, manufactured homes OK as well. (Buyer to verify.) Owners have critical area review approval letter. Lot certification complete with recording documents submitted to county. Perc test complete, onsite sewage permit approved as well. Lots are cleared, flat and ready for your new home build. Purchase one, purchase both!

Wake up to breathtaking sunrises & views of the marina and majestic mountains from this stunning home. As you step inside, you're greeted by vaulted wooden ceilings that create a warm atmosphere. French doors lead out to a balcony where you can enjoy your morning coffee while taking in the serene surroundings. The gourmet kitchen boasts a gas stove, elegant pendant lighting, & sleek stainless-steel appliances, perfect for culinary enthusiasts. The daylight basement level offers even more space to entertain or accommodate guests, featuring a large living area, full kitchen, bedroom, bath, and an extended private covered patio, ideal for outdoor gatherings or quiet relaxation. Shelter Bay amenities include sports courts, beach access & more!

Price Reduced!!! Charming residence boasting captivating views of Guemes Channel and San Juan Island ferry. The spacious open concept design with vaulted ceilings, accentuating a seamless flow throughout. Delight in the modern kitchen adorned with sleek subway tile and ss appliances, perfect for culinary endeavors. Step outside to discover a tranquil oasis, featuring tiered landscaping, a welcoming deck, and a designated raised garden bed area, ideal for outdoor enjoyment. Convenience meets functionality with a sizable laundry/mud room conveniently located adjacent to the garden space. Embrace the ease of access to the ferry, downtown amenities, and nearby state parks, making every day a delightful adventure in this remarkable home.
Nice treed lot with a 1968 singlewide, 48 feet long that needs some remodeling. Partially fenced yard. Large shop/garage which is partially locked.

Discover comfort and tranquility at 3907 Copper Pond. This well maintained home offers 3 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, and 1820 sq. ft. of living space, providing ample room for everyone. Enjoy sun-filled interiors, and spacious bedrooms. With top-rated schools and convenient access to amenities, this is the perfect retreat!

RARE EQUESTRIAN & ACREAGE ESTATE ON SOUGHT-AFTER LAKE CAMPBELL! The BEST of country living on stunning Fidalgo Island - all 10 mins from town! Home sits on 6.67 acres & has 365 views w/SPECTACULAR southern exposure, 280+ ft lakefront, 2 electric fully fenced pastures, 50' horse arena w/2-stall loafing shed & separate access road! Terraced grounds have garden space, orchard, enclosed chicken coop, vegetable beds, flagstone patio. Modern 3 bed, 3 bath home converted from 1960's barn has large 2-car garage, soaring 30+' ceilings w/exposed beams, stunning industrial staircase, concrete floors. Chefs kitchen w/solid maple cabinets, leathered granite counters, gas cooktop, W/I pantry. Front-row Mt. Erie views in primary bedroom w/spa-like bath!

Attention Investors! Alternatively, with some effort, you can transform it into your cozy abode. This property presents opportunities in the City of Burlington with zoning R-1-6-0. The three underlying lots can potentially be subdivided into three smaller lots or two larger lots. Verification by the buyer is required. The home offers 1900 square feet of living space with 4 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms on a corner lot. Sold As-Is. Newer roof and repair completed. Conveniently located in the town center, near I-5 and various amenities. Cash Sale!

There is no place like home! Move-in ready contemporary 2 bedroom/1.5 bath condo on second level. Covered patio off of the living room and over-looking a landscaped gated community courtyard. Covered parking and central location next to Skagit Valley Hospital and quick access to I-5. New carpet/flooring throughout and paint. Enjoy the wood fireplace with a view of the courtyard and a southerly territorial view from the dining room. New roof in 2023 and $290/mth HOA dues covers basic cable, water/sewer/garbage, common area maintenance, and lawn service.
